section.section:
In determining whether an applicant has voluntarily terminated coverage under an employer sponsored health benefit plan for purposes of paragraph (1) of this subsection, a voluntary termination may not be construed to include:
Loss of employment due to factors other than voluntary termination;
Change to a new employer that does not provide an option for dependent coverage;
Change of address so that no employer sponsored health benefit plan is available;
Discontinuation of health benefits to all dependents of employees of the applicant's employer; or
Expiration of the applicant's continuation of coverage under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA).
